The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | 48 arrested for mineral smuggling
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                      48 arrested for mineral smuggling
          OUR CORRESPONDENT                              
	Bhubaneswar, April 4: Cracking the whip on those involved in illegal mining and theft of minerals, the Keonjhar police have arrested the accused for illegally transporting nearly 152 rakes from Jurudi, Bansapani and Barbil railway sidings between January 1 and 25 this year.        
	The 48 people, arrested by Keonjhar police yesterday for allegedly smuggling rich minerals worth crores of rupees from the railway sidings, have been forwarded to court.         
	Those arrested include officials and representatives of private mining companies from Joda, Bamebari and Barbil, said Keonjhar SP Ashish Singh.         
	The cost of minerals would not be less than Rs 55.40 crore, he said, adding that they had also recovered thousands of tonnes of unclaimed iron and manganese ores near the railway sidings in the district.                                                                                                                                                           
